// PARSE-INVALID — Session 1.2 c.3 patch.
//
// The load-bearing case: a balanced brace pair containing a nested
// call inside the argument list. Before the c.3 patch this parsed
// as `x()` with the inner call to `y` SILENTLY LOST. After the patch
// the parser rejects with "Stray '{' inside call argument list".
//
// This is the case that motivated the patch: the Bismillah scope
// checker depends on CallRef extraction being complete. If a
// not_scope-violating call lived inside such a brace block, the
// pre-patch parser would silently strip it from the AST before the
// checker ever saw it — a Process-2 risk in the parser itself.
//
// Drill-down case 2 from the Perplexity parser review. If a future
// Phase ever introduces an expression grammar that legitimately
// uses braces inside calls (lambdas, blocks-as-expressions), this
// fixture migrates to ``valid/`` and the corresponding test
// inverts.

bismillah Sloppy {
    authority: NAMING_MD
    serves: purpose_hierarchy.truth_over_falsehood
    scope: orchestrate
    not_scope: parse_files
}

fn run() {
    x({ parse_files() })
}
